(225, 1, '2022-06-29 15:30:22', '2022-06-29 15:30:22', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"So, we are going back to the dungeon\" said Blaze.  \"Yes, but this is a different dungeon part,\" said Fireball.  \"It\'s sixty hallways.\"  \"What!\" said Blaze.  \"Yes, we have to go,\" said Fireball.  \"Do you want your mom and dad back or do you want to live with your brother for the rest of your life...and sister?\"  \"I\'m going to live with my mom and dad but I don\'t want to go back into the dungeon!\" said Blaze.  \"We have to if we want our mom and dad,\" said Fireball.  \"Ok, I guess so.  Let\'s go back to the dungeons!\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Six hours later: \"we\'re still walking?\" said Blaze.  \"Yeah\" replied Fireball.  \"We\'re not even at the dungeon!  We\'ve been walking in circles!\" said Blaze.  \"Ok, then let\'s just go this way\" said Fireball.  Thirty minutes later: \"We\'re finally at the dungeon and I know the door is going to close on us.  Then we\'re probably going to have to find the key and put the key in the door and walk sixty hallways down.  And then we\'re going to have to go sixty halls down again! And then we\'ll be able to get out.  We\'re also going to have to find out mom and dad.  Because it\'s probably not just sixty halls down.  It\'s probably like 61 halls down.  We\'re going to have to go 120 halls down! To be exact, 122 halls down! Well. let\'s get going!\" said Fireball.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Well here we go down the 122 halls,\" said Blaze.  One sixth of an hour later, \"Huh, huh!  Halfway, there.  Thirty halls down of sixty.  Then we\'ll have to do this all over again to get back,\" said Fireball.  \"Well, let\'s get going!\" said Blaze.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"They do it all again.  \"We\'re finally here\", said Fireball.  \"Where\'s our parents?\" \"Over there!\" replied Fireball.  \"Where?\" said Blaze and then he saw Fireball pointing at their parents.  And they saw their parents paralyzed.  They didn\'t know why they were paralyzed and they went over to where there parents were and then they said their real names, not mom and dad.  Their parents never replied and they noticed that they made a terrible mistake...pause...you know how they had a type of saw that could cut through those bars, well they threw it in a lava pit when they went out.  And now they have to find the key and it\'s waaaay over at the guards break place.  They had to go ver there to take the key but it was super far away and they had to keep walking.  They walked and walked and walked.  They seemed to never get there.  But then they noticed that they were just going in circles.  They had to go into the middle where no one knew how to get in.  Then they went back to the door.  They knew it was close but they put the key in a box that they found near the door.  So they just took the key out and unlocked the door.  Once they were out they went over to where they knew the metal was but the didn \'t know how to get in but then they saw a green button.  They pressed it and a trap door formed under there feet and they fell into the middle... </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once they were down there they saw a box in the middle of the room.  They knew that was the room to get the key but they had to get an other key to get in.  But luckily the guards were very lazy and never hid it.  So the key was already in the door.  So they just went in.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When they were in there they couldn\'t find the key anywhere. Then they noticed that the guards weren\'t lazy. They put the key there on purpose se they could get in but then they hid the key super good.  And they didn\'t notice that the door closed right behind them.  Good thing the room was giant so they could find it anywhere.  And at least they had some water so they could find the three keys they needed...pause...here are the names of the three keys, well not exactly.  One of the three keys is supposed to be the one for the door to get out.  The second one was how they were supposed to get out of the room.  And the last one was for their parents.  So they had to find all three keys...unpause...Fireball eventually found one of the keys, Blaze found another.  They had two keys, the didn\'t know what they were both for.  They had to get the last one.  But first they went over to the door to see if one of them opened it.  And none of them did.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ten hours later: Fireball and Blaze couldn\'t find the last key.  It was hidden very well.  Ten more hours later: they finally found the key!  And then they took a burrito break.  After the burrito break, they went back to the door.  They unlocked it with one of the keys.  Then they got out of the room by digging there way because they found a shovel in there.  And then they were back at the surface.  They went through the door again which closed right behind them again.  They went back through the 122 halls again and then they were back at their parents.  They unlocked the door and dragged there parents all the way to the door because they were paralyzed.  They unlocked the door and went back home.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After they were back home their parents weren\'t paralyzed anymore.  Once they asked how they got paralyzed their parents said that there was a paralyzing field that was around the dungeon.  And the parents also wondered one thing too, well actually three.  First they asked where Fireball and Blaze\'s sister was.  Then, they asked how they got Blaze out.  And last, they asked how Fireball and Blaze weren\'t paralyzed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Check back on www.finneas.fuzzylojic.com to see our latest book: Fireball Book 6; Fireball\'s Birthday.  But if you want to know how old he is going to be, he is going to be 11.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Fireball Book 5 - Back to the Dungeon', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'fireball-book-5-back-to-the-dungeon', '', '', '2022-10-05 15:11:25', '2022-10-05 15:11:25', '', 0, 'https://finneas.fuzzylojic.com/?p=225', 0, 'post', '', 3),
